              "settings": {
                "heading": "How does the UNNAP Device work?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_dctg93": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>The UNNAP device is a small, engraved NFC device. Place it somewhere away from your bed — like the kitchen or bathroom. When the alarm rings, you must tap your phone on the UNNAP device to stop it. This physical movement helps you avoid hitting snooze and going back to sleep.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "normal",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
